  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Family of bankers and land and timber speculators from Ionia, Michigan; two brothers, Angelo E. and Osmond S. Tower served as captains in Co. E, 6th Michigan Cavalry during the Civil War; Osmond S. Tower later became president of the First National Bank of Ionia; Angelo Tower was active in timber investment in Washington State.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Civil War correspondence and other related documents of Angelo E. Tower; miscellaneous financial records and correspondence of Angelo and Osmond Tower concerning banking and commerce in Ionia, and timber speculation in Washington State; also other business materials, primarily banking, of Louis S. Lovell, W. B. Heath, and George W. Webber.</subfield>
